Mapping each base64 char to one word seems rather inefficient. If you have a longer list of N swears (say 256 because it&#x27;s the size of a byte, making encoding easier), you could produce a more efficient base-N encoding, e.g.:<p><pre><code>  var bytes = atob(base64msg),
      swearsMsg = &#x27;&#x27;;
  for (var i = 0; i < bytes.length; i++) {
      newMsg += swears[bytes[i].charAt(0)] + &#x27; &#x27;;
  }
</code></pre>
Of course, it&#x27;s still less efficient than base64, but it&#x27;s an improvement. :)
